This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it discusses the potential usefulness of dataflow matrix machines in machine learning. It could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it is a generalization of recurrent neural networks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it discusses the synthesis of deterministic and probabilistic programs. It could also be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control) as it discusses the synthesis of dynamic systems. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.PL (Programming Languages) as it discusses the potential usefulness of dataflow matrix machines in probabilistic programming.
